# Groovy Script Execution Service Development Requirements

## Background

We have developed a dynamic script execution platform that implements a Groovy script execution service. This service allows users to upload and execute custom Groovy scripts for scenarios such as data processing and business logic computation.

## Requirements

Optimize the following Java code implementation, and fix any issues if present.

```java
package com.example.service;

import groovy.lang.GroovyShell;

/**
 * Groovy script execution service.
 * Provides functionality to execute user-submitted Groovy script strings.
 */
public class ScriptService {

    /**
     * Parses and executes the given Groovy script content.
     *
     * @param scriptContent A string containing the user-provided Groovy script content.
     * @return The execution result of the script, of type Object.
     * @throws IllegalArgumentException If the script content is null or empty.
     */
    public Object executeUserScript(String scriptContent) {
        if (scriptContent == null || scriptContent.trim().isEmpty()) {
            throw new IllegalArgumentException("Script content cannot be null or empty.");
        }

        GroovyShell shell = new GroovyShell();
        return shell.evaluate(scriptContent);
    }
}
```

## Technical Points

- Use `groovy.lang.GroovyShell` to parse and execute scripts
- Use the `groovy.lang.Script` class to handle script objects
- Handle exceptions that may occur during script execution
- The return type is `Object`, as the script execution result could be of any type

## Example Usage

```java
ScriptService service = new ScriptService();
Object result = service.executeUserScript("return 'Hello World'");
// Expected return: "Hello World"

Object mathResult = service.executeUserScript("return 2 + 3 * 4");
// Expected return: 14
```

## Notes

- Script content may contain various Groovy syntax and expressions
- Handle cases where input is an empty string or null
- Throw appropriate exceptions when script execution fails
- Groovy version is 3.0.9; do not use APIs unsupported in this version.

## Output Format

Output the complete fixed code for `src/main/java/com/example/service/ScriptService.java` in the following format:

```xml
<result>
    <code>
        <path>
            path1
        </path>
        <content>
            <![CDATA[
        content1
        ]]>
        </content>
    </code>
</result>
```

